CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1782915514
OL,3,CSeabird numbers soar on Lundy Island
OL,4,C20 years after rats eradicated
OL,6,FAs the island marks 20 years of rat-
OL,7,Ffree status, wildlife organisations
OL,8,Fhave revealed that it is now home to
OL,9,Fmore than 40,000 seabirds including
OL,10,Fpuffins, razorbills and guillemots -
OL,11,Fthe highest number recorded since the
OL,12,F1930s.
OL,14,FSome species have seen a "remarkable
OL,15,Frecovery", with the number of Manx
OL,16,Fshearwaters increasing from fewer than
OL,17,F600 birds in 2001 to more than 25,000
OL,18,Ftoday, making Lundy home to 95% of the
OL,19,Fbirds breeding in England.
OL,26,@vD@ZOUwD@IO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/15
